Description: Fragment of rim of Attic red-figured pottery bell- or calyx-krater. Part of laurel wreath preserved on outside of rim; reserved band at top of rim inside. Incised inscription on top.
Curator's comments: Almost certainly from same vase as 1886,0401.942.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 575)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1131)
